        <!-- Architecture -->
        <div class="project-section alt-bg">
            <h3>Architecture Explanation</h3>
            <p>The architecture implements a production-ready static website:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>S3 Primary Bucket</strong> – Hosts website files (index.html, style.css, images/).</li>
                <li><strong>Static Website Hosting</strong> – Serves files as a public website endpoint.</li>
                <li><strong>Bucket Policy</strong> – Allows public read access (s3:GetObject) for all objects.</li>
                <li><strong>Versioning</strong> – Maintains multiple versions of files for recovery.</li>
                <li><strong>Lifecycle Rules</strong> – Moves old versions to cheaper storage, deletes expired files.</li>
                <li><strong>Cross-Region Replication</strong> – Copies objects to a backup bucket in another region.</li>
                <li><strong>Access Logs Bucket</strong> – Stores server access logs for analysis.</li>
                <li><strong>CloudTrail</strong> – Records all S3 API calls (uploads, downloads, deletes).</li>
                <li><strong>Lambda Function</strong> – Triggered on S3 uploads for event-driven automation.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

